---
import { getCollection } from 'astro:content';
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const allProjects = await getCollection('projects');
const projectsBySlug = new Map(allProjects.map((project) => [project.id, project]));
const currentlyBuildingSlugs = [
  'ai-blueprint',
  'vidpipe',
  'multiprompter',
  'mission-control',
  'bradtraversy-dev',
  'stackmaven',
];
const currentlyBuilding = currentlyBuildingSlugs
  .map((slug) => projectsBySlug.get(slug))
  .filter((project) => project !== undefined);

// Manual focus notes per project (1-line "what's the active push here").
// Update these when the focus shifts; if a project isn't listed, the card
// still renders with its tagline as fallback.
const focusNotes: Record<string, string> = {
  'ai-blueprint':
    'turning the blueprint into the default workflow layer: clearer gates, better resumes, status/check/adopt flows, and real use on active builds.',
  vidpipe:
    'back in the product lane. seo prerendering is in, publishing destinations are the next serious feature, and the bundle needs a cleanup pass.',
  multiprompter:
    'mac teleprompter experiment. one script driving multiple synced viewer windows, built for recording setups where the script has to follow me.',
  'mission-control':
    'still the private ops surface for the vault. current arc is making the automation fleet easier to see, trust, and hand work to.',
  'bradtraversy-dev':
    'using the site as the public trail for what shipped: articles, devlogs, project pages, and the small tool catalog.',
  stackmaven:
    'background publication lane. keep the quality bar, but it is not the main sprint while product work gets the deeper block.',
};

const lastUpdated = '2026-06-29';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="now | brad traversy"
  description="what i'm actively working on right now."
  pageTitle="now.md"
  currentSection="now"
>
  <section class="section">
    <h1 class="h1"><span class="hash"># </span>now</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      what i'm focused on right this minute. updated when the focus shifts.
      see the date at the bottom for the last revision.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2 class="h2"><span class="hash">## </span>right now</h2>
    <p>
      main focus: using <a href="/projects/ai-blueprint" class="link">ai blueprint</a>
      as the workflow layer for real builds, not just as a repo template. the
      goal is to make planning, implementation, checking, status, and adoption
      feel repeatable enough that every product block starts with the same
      rails.
    </p>
    <p>
      product-wise, <a href="/projects/vidpipe" class="link">vidpipe</a> is back
      near the top of the list. the public pages are crawlable now, the model
      routing is cleaner, and the next useful push is publishing: wordpress
      first, then the rest only if the workflow earns it.
    </p>
    <p>
      <a href="/projects/multiprompter" class="link">multiprompter</a> is the
      smaller build i keep wanting for recording: one script, multiple synced
      windows, less awkward script-reading during videos. still beta, but it is
      the right kind of personal tool.
    </p>
    <p>
      the automation fleet also got rebuilt around a cleaner orchestrator and
      separate work lanes. that matters less as a public product and more as the
      operating layer under the rest of the work. i wrote the current shape up
      in <a href="/articles/my-agent-stack-changed-again" class="link">my agent stack changed again</a>.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2 class="h2"><span class="hash">## </span>currently building</h2>
    <div class="comment">
      // featured + active projects, with the current push on each
    </div>
    <div class="now-projects">
      {currentlyBuilding.map((project) => (
        <a class="now-project" href={`/projects/${project.id}`}>
          <div class="now-project-head">
            <span class="now-project-name">{project.data.name}</span>
            <span class:list={['pill', project.data.status]}>{project.data.status}</span>
          </div>
          <p class="now-project-note">
            {focusNotes[project.id] ?? project.data.tagline}
          </p>
        </a>
      ))}
    </div>
    <a href="/projects" class="link more-link">→ all projects</a>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2 class="h2"><span class="hash">## </span>what i'm thinking about</h2>
    <ul class="prose-list">
      <li>
        how much of product work can be turned into a calm blueprint workflow
        without making it feel like ceremony. the sweet spot is just enough
        structure that the ai does not drift
      </li>
      <li>
        whether vidpipe is a product problem or a distribution problem. the
        crawlable-site work fixed the technical floor; now the question is
        whether the publishing flow is useful enough to push harder
      </li>
      <li>
        personal tools as unfair advantages. multiprompter, linesmith,
        typesmith, and the agent workflow are all small things that make
        recording and building less annoying
      </li>
      <li>
        stackmaven is still interesting, but it is lower in the stack right now:
        maintain the editorial lane, avoid filler, and let the automation catch
        the high-signal stuff while the product work gets the deeper focus
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2 class="h2"><span class="hash">## </span>what i'm not doing</h2>
    <ul class="prose-list">
      <li>no live coding sessions or live streams right now</li>
      <li>not chasing every shiny model release. only swap when there's a real reason</li>
      <li>not building a course platform. that's not what this site is for</li>
      <li>no new sponsor commitments beyond existing ones</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <p class="comment-prose">
      // last updated <strong>{lastUpdated}</strong>. inspired by{' '}
      <a href="https://nownownow.com/about" class="link">/now pages</a>.
    </p>
  </section>

  <div class="comment" style="margin-top: 24px;">
    // EOF now.md<span class="cursor"></span>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .now-projects {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 12px;
    margin-top: 12px;
  }
  .now-project {
    display: block;
    padding: 14px 16px;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 6px;
    background: var(--bg-2);
    text-decoration: none;
    color: var(--fg-1);
    transition: border-color 0.12s ease, background 0.12s ease;
  }
  .now-project:hover {
    border-color: var(--border-strong);
    background: var(--bg-3, var(--bg-2));
  }
  .now-project-head {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 12px;
  }
  .now-project-name {
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 14px;
  }
  .now-project-note {
    margin: 6px 0 0;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    font-size: 13px;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
  .prose-list {
    margin: 12px 0 16px;
    padding-left: 20px;
    list-style: disc;
    color: var(--fg-1);
  }
  .prose-list li {
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }
  .comment-prose {
    color: var(--fg-comment);
    font-size: 12.5px;
  }
</style>
